.asoundrc
configures 4-channel input & output ALSA devices.
Copy to /home/root 

default.pa
this file tells PulseAudio to load the virtual ALSA device.
Copy to /etc/pulse

client.conf
disables PulseAudio server respawning.
Copy to /etc/pulse

Usage:
1) To capture 4 channels with arecord:
arecord -D plug:multicapture -c 4 -r 16000 -f s16_le testcapture.wav

2) To capture 4 channels with parec:
parec -r --channels=4 --rate=16000 --format=s16le -d alsa_input.multicapture testcapture.raw
parec --device=alsa_input.multicapture --channels=4 --rate=16000 --format=s16le  testcapture.raw

3) To playback 4 channels with parec:
parec -p --device=alsa_output.0.analog-stereo --format=s16le --channels=4 --rate=16000 testcapture.raw

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
connection-id: create stream to pass the name of property.


